cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed systems and algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new definition of minimal dominating set and provides a necessary and sufficient condition for its construction. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses communication in distributed systems. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and network dynamics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new measure of time complexity in time-varying graphs.
